snippet.textDisplay:
I worked for Weta Digital on LOTR and was involved in the early motion control and forced perspective tests. Brain Van't Hul, who was the head of the VFX camera department, figured out the scaling techniques and how to sync the moving platform to the motion of the camera. The guy is a genius!

This was my first job working for a VFX company. I still can believe how lucky I was to have had the chance to work on such well loved and ground breaking movies.
snippet.textOriginal:
I worked for Weta Digital on LOTR and was involved in the early motion control and forced perspective tests. Brain Van't Hul, who was the head of the VFX camera department, figured out the scaling techniques and how to sync the moving platform to the motion of the camera. The guy is a genius!

This was my first job working for a VFX company. I still can believe how lucky I was to have had the chance to work on such well loved and ground breaking movies.
